            <scopecontent id="aspace_124de885593dfff632a14d470d3dcc6b">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>William H. Potter's journals contain descriptions of his activities and discourses on religious and political subjects. There is also a diary, 1859-1861, and other materials of (his daughter?) Kittie Potter and an unidentified judicial diary dated 1933. Potter's letters to Thomas E. Packer in the 1850s are in the Thomas E. Packer Papers, Manuscript Group No. 1010.</p>
            </scopecontent>
